Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 200 degrees. Thinly slice the @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Remove and discard the @Tuscan kale{4%ounce} ribs and stems. Roughly chop the leaves. Thinly slice the @scallions{2} greens and whites. Mince the @garlic{2%clove}. Slice half the @polenta{1%unit} into ½-inch rounds.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of @olive oil{8%teaspoon} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the polenta rounds. Cook ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until golden brown and slightly crispy. Set aside the cooked polenta on a #baking sheet{}. Sprinkle with @Gruyère cheese{1/2%cup}, and transfer to the oven to warm.

> You may need to work in batches, depending on the size of your pan.

Discard all but a thin layer of olive oil from the pan before heating over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until soft and golden brown. Add the scallions and garlic. Cook another ~{1-2%minutes}, until fragrant. Add the kale and a splash of @water{a splash}. Cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes}, until soft and golden.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in the same pan over medium heat. Once hot, crack the @eggs{2} into the pan, and fry until the edges begin to turn golden brown. Reduce heat to low. Cover the pan for ~{1%minute}, until whites are set but yolks are still runny. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Add a few teaspoons of water to the pan before covering to steam the eggs and speed up the cooking.

Finish: Plate the cheesy polenta cakes. Top with the kale mushroom hash, eggs, and a sprinkle of @hot smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}. Enjoy!